Male palp (
Figs 36–38
): upper distal corner of conductor close to tegular process, incrassate and slightly folded downwards, with tip pointed in retrolateral view.

Vulva (
Figs 29–33
): atrium short, with two almost round lateral patches of pores; receptacula pyriform, with short basal stalks, and median pair larger than lateral pair.
